My, my, young lady. Thank you for
patronizing us again today.\n< Receptionist >

If you're going to take a bath, please
take a wooden tag with you.\n< Receptionist >

Ah, if it isn't Lady Serena. Please, by
all means, enjoy the hot springs again
today.\n< Henry >

...I must say something or I won't be
satisfied!\n< Serena >

\n< Serena >Is the proprietor here? I heard one can
take a bath here.
\n< Receptionist >Oh, welcome... Oh?
\n< Serena >...What is it?
モブ HK_温泉主人01-1
モブ HK_温泉主人01-1

Ah, no... hehe, such a splendid
blonde... I mean, you have an unfamiliar
face.\n< Receptionist >

It's not unusual to have guests from
outside, is it?\n< Serena >

Heh, heh. Well, that's true, but it's
not often we get someone of your...
caliber.\n< Receptionist >
\n< Serena >...?

Well, it's fine. This is my first time
using a public bathhouse.\n< Serena >

Since I'm not familiar with the customs,
I would like an explanation.\n< Serena >

Eh? Explanation... Well, there aren't
really any significant rules...\n< Receptionist >

Even if there aren't significant rules,
there must be some minor ones, right?\n< Serena >

So, first of all, how many attendants
will there be?\n< Serena >
Attendants...?\n< Receptionist >
Yes...?\n< Serena >

Umm... about how to enter the water...
is that what you're asking?\n< Receptionist >

If so, first you should proceed to the
changing room.\n< Receptionist >
Hmm.\n< Serena >

There, you take off your clothes, put
them in a basket, close the door, and
oh, this wooden piece acts as a key so
don't forget it.\n< Receptionist >
Understood.\n< Serena >

Then you take a towel with you to the
bath area and soak in the tub and...
well, that's how it goes.\n< Receptionist >
Eh... alone?\n< Serena >
Yes, usually alone.\n< Receptionist >
In the nude...?\n< Serena >
Generally, yes, in the nude.\n< Receptionist >
That's... impossible...\n< Serena >
Would you like to leave then?\n< Receptionist >

Are there no other baths in this
town...?\n< Serena >

Otherwise, there are some who fancy
taking a dip in the river...\n< Receptionist >
That's even more impossible...\n< Serena >

Grr... but I can't just not bathe for
the entire stay...\n< Serena >

No, to begin with, I can't even endure
just this one day.\n< Serena >
Then... I must... resolve myself...!\n< Serena >
The rumored... solo bath...!\n< Serena >

The bath area is mixed bathing, with men
entering as well\n< Receptionist >

Men enter as well?! That's indecent! A
terrible thing will happen!\n< Serena >

...which is why we've received many such
complaints, so now there's a partition
in the middle.\n< Receptionist >

However, it's a simple construction done
by amateurs, so please don't lean on it
too much.\n< Receptionist >

Well, if that's the case then it's fine.
I won't go near it even if asked.\n< Serena >
\n< Receptionist >So, what will you do?
I'll enter... I'm going in!\n< Serena >

Yes, now I am an adventurer. An
adventurer, one who braves the
treacherous.\n< Serena >

No matter what happens, I will
splendidly overcome this perilous
crisis.\n< Serena >
Well then.\n< Receptionist >
The women's bath is to your right.\n< Receptionist >

The bathing fee is included in the
lodging cost.\n< Receptionist >

Please take one of the wooden tags from
that box and enjoy your bath at your
leisure.\n< Receptionist >
Hmm, thank you, innkeeper-dono.\n< Serena >
モブ HK_温泉主人01-1
モブ HK_温泉主人01-1

Excuse me for asking so soon, but where
is the changing room...? I don't see a
specific room anywhere.\n< Serena >

You are standing right in it as we
speak.\n< Receptionist >
Here?!?\n< Serena >

It's not a room, and there isn't even a
threshold! Everything can be seen...!\n< Serena >
Sigh, but everyone does it this way...\n< Receptionist >

Ah, that reminds me, lately the young
ladies have been using this to cover
their skin while changing.\n< Receptionist >
\n< Serena >...A towel, huh. It's quite small...

\n< Serena >...I wish there was something a bit
more...
Everyone does it this way...\n< Receptionist >

...Ugh, am I making an unreasonable
request? I'm sorry, thank you.\n< Serena >
No, not at all...\n< Receptionist >

I have no choice but to make do with
this. Somehow...\n< Serena >
That's the rule, after all...\n< Serena >

Oh my... this is...\n< Receptionist >
\n< Serena >...Ugh...uh...

\n< Serena >Once I take this off, I'll be truly
naked... Only a towel to shield my
body...

Ugh! Is this really okay...?! To
undress... here?! In such a place...!\n< Serena >

This is a critical moment in life...!
I'm ascending the stairs to
adulthood...!\n< Serena >

Father and mother surely cannot even
dream that I am doing such a thing in
such a place right now...!\n< Serena >
Grr...!\n< Serena >
\n< Serena >Haah...haah...

I'm naked, truly naked... In such a
place, alone, outside of the mansion...\n< Serena >

My heart's beating so loud...! Can it be
heard by those around me?\n< Serena >

I'm more nervous than when I left home
alone, than when I fought goblins, far
more nervous...\n< Serena >

It feels like I'm doing something very
bad...!\n< Serena >

Hurry up and finish, yes, just finish
quickly.\n< Serena >

What's the big deal? It's said that all
commoners do it this way.\n< Serena >
\n< Serena >This is the men's changing room.

*panting* I... I need to get to the
changing room... to get my clothes...\n< Serena >

(There are... there are male guests here
too!? ...Uuuu~!!!!)\n< Serena >

\n< Receptionist >Oh my, young lady. What seems to be the
matter?

\n< Serena >Th-the door to the sauna, it's... right
now...

Ah, did you use the sauna? How was it?
We've recently introduced it. It's been
quite popular with our guests...\n< Receptionist >
No, that's not what I mean...\n< Serena >

Looking at you, young lady, it seems
you've enjoyed yourself quite a bit...
Your porcelain- like white skin is moist
and flushed, and you're steaming nicely,
aren't you?\n< Receptionist >
\n< Serena >Ah, uh... don't look!
\n< Serena >Uuuu~~~!
\n< Receptionist >...Hmm?
...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >
\n< Serena >...This is the worst day of my life...

\n< Serena >...To be subjected to... such an
ordeal...

...I must say something or I won't be
satisfied!\n< Serena >

My, my, young lady. What seems to be the
matter? You're out of breath.\n< Receptionist >
\n< Serena >What's the matter, you ask...!

Receptionist! I wasn't informed that the
sauna was unisex!\n< Serena >

And, on top of that, there was no
doorknob on the women's side...! Because
of that, I...!\n< Serena >

You must have seen everything that
happened...!\n< Serena >

Oh dear... That is quite unfortunate. It
seems we've neglected to explain
properly.\n< Receptionist >

Regarding the sauna's door on the
women's side, are you saying you
couldn't open it because there was no
doorknob?\n< Receptionist >

That's exactly what I'm saying! It's a
serious issue! Fix it at once! Surely
there have been other complaints!\n< Serena >
Well, about that...\n< Receptionist >

The door on the women's side of the
sauna can be opened by inserting a
wooden tag and turning it.\n< Receptionist >
Everyone uses it that way...\n< Receptionist >

What? Why... why would it be like
that...\n< Serena >

Well, if we didn't do it that way, men
could just go through the sauna and
enter the women's bath.\n< Receptionist >

Around here, it's common sense, so I
just forgot to explain. My apologies.\n< Receptionist >

It's common sense, you see? I just
carelessly forgot to warn you... Please
forgive me... hehe...\n< Receptionist >

Ngh, grr... So that's how it is... If
it's common sense... then my ignorance
is also to blame...\n< Serena >

Hehehe... Have you come to understand,
young lady?\n< Receptionist >

...I've suffered a humiliation so severe
I thought I might die. I can't easily
accept this...\n< Serena >

I can't accept it, but I can't add to my
shame either... I will... sheathe my
sword.\n< Serena >

Sigh... For the next ten years, I'll
probably be tossing and turning in bed
remembering today...\n< Serena >

As expected of a young lady of your
stature.\n< Receptionist >

...I've been meaning to ask, but what is
this 'young lady' you keep referring to?\n< Serena >

Hehe... Well, it's just that your unique
aura and dignified presence make one
naturally refer to you as such.\n< Receptionist >

Is that so. But if you're going to
address me, 'Serena' will do. Being
called 'young lady' by an unfamiliar man
is rather embarrassing.\n< Serena >

Oh my... Serena-sama, my name is Henry,
and though I am but a commoner without a
family name, please allow me to
reintroduce myself...\n< Henry >

Very well. Then Henry-dono, let us say
that today's unfortunate
misunderstanding... I will try... to be
understanding.\n< Serena >

So this is merely an opinion as a user,
but I think some sort of notice about
the doorknob mechanism is necessary.\n< Serena >

If needed, I am willing to contribute to
the cost for such a notice.\n< Serena >

Hehe. I've reflected on this as well.
It's just a matter of writing a quick
note with a brush. It won't cost as much
as you think.\n< Henry >

We'll add a note when we get the chance,
and if that resolves the issue for now,
we would be most grateful.\n< Receptionist >

Very well. That would indeed allow me to
use the facilities with peace of mind.\n< Serena >
Then, if you'll excuse me.\n< Serena >

Hehe, please continue to favor us in the
future. Serena-sama.\n< Henry >
Just some trivial documents.\n< Serena >

It doesn't seem like there's much to see
here.\n< Serena >
It's alcohol.\n< Serena >

A drink after a bath. Erika-sama says
it's irresistible.\n< Serena >

Will I eventually become like that too?
Hmm...\n< Serena >
Hm? There's a hole here.\n< Serena >
What's this...?\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

It's too dark to see clearly, but
there's a bad vibe coming from it...
It's creepy. Let's stay away.\n< Serena >
